DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       Ecatools  are  simple  command  line utils that do various
       audio processing tasks. Most of them  support  batch  pro-
       cessing. They all use the ecasound engine (libecasound).

       EECCAAPPLLAAYY

       A  simple  command-line  tool that plays input files using
       the default output specified in _~_/_._e_c_a_s_o_u_n_d_r_c.

       EECCAACCOONNVVEERRTT

       A tool for converting a set of files to  a  common  target
       format.   This target format is given as the first command
       line argument, and its syntax is _._e_x_t.

       EECCAAFFIIXXDDCC

       A simple command-line tool for fixing DC-offset.

       EECCAANNOORRMMAALLIIZZEE

       A simple command-line tool for normalizing sample  volume.
       Finds  out  how  much  input file can be amplified without
       clipping and, if necessary, does the amplification.

       EECCAASSIIGGNNAALLVVIIEEWW

       Ecasignalview is meant for monitoring signal amplitude and
       peak statistics. It accepts the following options:


       input  The  first option not starting with a '-' is inter-
              preted as input string. This can be a device  or  a
              filename.  All formats supported by libecasound are
              accepted. Defaults to '/dev/dsp'.





